===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|bible}}, from Middle {{der|en|la|-}} {{m|la|biblia||book}} (misinterpreted as a feminine from earlier Latin neuter plural {{m|la|biblia||books}}), from {{der|en|grc|βιβλία||books}}, plural of {{m|grc|βιβλίον||small book}}, originally a diminutive of {{m|grc|βίβλος||book}}, from {{m|grc|βύβλος||papyrus}} (from the ancient [[Phoenicia]]n city of ''[[Byblos]]'' which exported this writing material).

Old English used {{m|ang|biblioþece|biblioþēce}} (from [[βιβλιοθήκη]]) and {{m|ang|gewritu|ġewritu}} (> English {{m|en|writs}}) for "the Scriptures".

